    "King, born in Baltimore, MD, was the son of Henry Stauffer King (1849-1943), president of Baltimore Trust Company, and Ella Wynn (King) (1858-1935).": [],
    "At eight years old, Edward attended a reception with his father, where he first met Henry Walters (1848-1931), founder of the Walters Art Gallery.": [],
    "King was educated at the Boys' Latin School, where he befriended <a href=\"https://arthistorians.info/barra/\">Alfred H. Barr Jr.</a>, the future founding director of the Museum of Modern Art.": [],
    "He graduated in 1918 and, at Barr\u2019s urging, transferred from Johns Hopkins to Princeton, where he studied under <a href=\"https://arthistorians.info/moreyc/\">Charles Rufus Morey</a>.": [],
